Sequence Information.Family: Belongs to the frog skin active peptide family (Brevinin subfamily)
Sequence Information.Target Organism: Gram-negative bacterium:Escherichia coli K12;Gram-positive bacterium:Micrococcus luteus NCT C2665.
Sequence Information.Hemolytic Activity: No hemolysis information or data found in the reference(s) presented in this entry
Sequence Information.Comments: Mast cell degranulating peptide. Causes histamine release from rat peritoneal mast cells in vitro.

Literature.Title: Histamine-releasing and antimicrobial peptides from the skin secretions of the dusky gopher frog, Rana sevosa.
Literature.Author: Graham C, Richter SC, McClean S, O'Kane E, Flatt PR, Shaw C.
